shlokas.english:
The nine states (Avasthas) of a planet are: 
1. Deeptha (radiant) when in its sign of exaltation;
2. Stimitha (calm/steady) in its own sign;
3. Muditha (happy) in the sign of an intimate friend (Adhimitra);
4. Shanta (peaceful) in a friend's (Mitra) sign;
5. Heena (deficient) in a neutral's (Sama) sign;
6. Duhkha (miserable/pained) in an enemy's (Satru) sign;
7. Vikala (distressed/mutilated) when conjoined with a malefic;
8. Khala (wicked/ruined) when defeated in planetary war; and
9. Kopa (angry/furious) when combust (conjoined with the Sun).
